      },
      "title": "",
      "description": "An ode to cricket \n\nPeople say cricket is a religion\nActually for us the now grown up kids of the 90s cricket is an emotion.\n\nIt is a memory that we live relive endlessly and every time we play the recording in our head there is fountain of joy that bursts. \n\nWhen sachin hit Qadir for those 3 6s in Pakistan\nWhen jaedja hit 40 runs of 2 overs in wc\nWhen Prasad got Sohail out\nWhen Sachin hit the mighty aussies out of the park at sharjah\nWhen sachin scored 140 against Kenya after his father's death\nWhen ganguly waved his t shirt at lords\nWhen India lost the 2003 wc final\nThen the loss against bdesh in 2007\nDhoni and co winning the maiden 2007 T20\n2011 wc win with that 6 from dhoni.....\n\nWe the kids of 90s feel we hv grown up and outgrown cricket but then come these moments that bring back the childlike joy out of us.\n\nWhen at midnight u shout like a kid when klaasen and miller get out (I actuslly did to bring my daughter out of their stupor) the same way u did when prasad bowled Sohail inn1996. And it is in these moments that yr heart says\n\n Abhi mujhme kahi Baaki thodi si hai zindagi.\n\nThank u cricket for letting the child in us be alive and kicking and reminding us from time to time\n\n An adult is nothing but an overgrown child\n\nIn a life otherwise full of the dull and mundane with some moments of individuals highs and lows, cricket is one thing that brings unforgettable  collective joy and happiness across the country. Experiencing live the impromptu celebrations on streets of Kolkata was a such a moment of joy.\n\nThank u cricket for no other aspect of life has given us more joy than you.",
      "dubbing_info": [
        
      ],
      "media_variants": [
        
      ]
    },
    {
