      },
      "title": "",
      "description": "A tribute to Dravid\n\nIf cricket is a gentleman's game then that gentleman has to be Rahul Dravid. Can't think of another person who has carried himself with the same poise, elegance, dedication and commitment like he has done. But did cricket serve him what he deserved - not really. The biggest and perhaps the only major success (as a team) of his life came on the last day of his association with cricket - both life and cricket at times can be really testing and cruel and the it's best students are put through the most stringent tests. And when life tests us let's a be dravid and not a Gandhi (dig intended).\n\nThank you Mr Dravid for showing us that life can he lived like this too that game can be played like this too both as a player and as a coach and the more committed you are more it will test you but there is redemption at the end sometimes at the very end.\n\nIf I had a son i would have liked him to become like rahul Dravid in whatever vocation/profession he chose.\n\nQuoting shakespeare\n\nHis life was gentle; and the elements\nSo mixed in him, that Nature might stand up\nAnd say to all the world, THIS WAS A MAN!\n\nThat man to me/us is Rahul Dravid",
      "dubbing_info": [
        
      ],
      "media_variants": [
        
      ]
